{
  "text": "Finally, data on the value of the 12-lead ECG for predicting the underlying substrate for VTs arising from the RV are scarce. Hoffmayer et al 28 compared the 12-lead ECG morphology of VTs with LBBB and inferior axis from 42 patients with idiopathic RV outflow tract VT and 16 with arrhythmogenic RV cardiomyopathy. The duration of the QRS in lead I \u2265120 ms, earliest onset of QRS in lead V1, presence of QRS notching in at least 1 lead, and a precordial transition at V 5 or later were independent predictors of arrhythmogenic RV cardiomyopathy. Using these ECG features during VT and the presence/absence of negative T waves in leads V1-V3 during sinus rhythm, the same authors constructed a risk score for arrhythmogenic RV cardiomyopathy. [CITATION_1] A score of \u22655 (maximum score, 8 points) identified arrhythmogenic RV cardiomyopathy as underlying substrate for VT with a positive predictive value of 100% and a negative PV of 91%.",
